HEADWORD: Hydronephrosis
<hw>Hy`dro*ne*phro"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
Gr. <grk>"y`dwr</grk> water + <?/ a kidney.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An accumulation of urine in the pelvis of the kidney, occasioned by
obstruction in the urinary passages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

